This paper discusses decoding algorithms for polar codes, which are a type of error-correcting code used in information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). However, the paper also discusses Reed-Muller codes, which are a type of error-correcting code used in computer science, so cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses complexity analysis of the decoding algorithms, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as polar codes are used in wireless communication systems.
